Azure provides multiple data migration options to help organizations move data from on-premises environments or other cloud platforms into Azure efficiently and securely.

These options include:

* Online migration tools (over network)
* Offline migration tools (physical devices)
* Hybrid approaches

For example, small datasets can be migrated over the internet, while large datasets may require offline transfer using physical devices.

A real-life use case is a company migrating its on-premise database to Azure SQL Database.

Another example is moving large backup archives to Azure Blob Storage.

Choosing the right migration method depends on data size, network bandwidth, and time constraints.
